    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but i've tried looking closer and the \"processing power\" thing doesn't explain why certain things just... stop making sense. like i'll be looking at a building and the texture just looks flat for a second before it snaps back. if there's a way to actually test this, though, how would someone even do that? if i wanted to see if the environment is actually struggling to render, what kind of things would i look for? like, what are the logical indicators that a simulation is hitting its ceiling?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
