      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "If you were to look for indicators of a rendering issue, you might observe moments of digital artifacting, like sudden, brief texture flickering or inconsistent physics in moving objects. Another sign could be environmental repetition that is too perfect, like repeating background loops that lack natural variation. However, these phenomena are often explained by the way our brains process overwhelming stimuli, which can create distortions that mimic technical failures.",
